WEBVTT

00:01.727 --> 00:02.817
<i> - Previously</i>
<i> on "Fantasy Island"...</i>

00:02.895 --> 00:03.910
<i> - Ruby, this is</i>
<i> Ms. Elena Roarke.</i>

00:04.063 --> 00:05.153
- Welcome to Fantasy Island.

00:05.231 --> 00:06.988
<i> I can't cure your cancer.</i>

00:07.066 --> 00:10.250
- I'm looking for a fantasy,
not a miracle.

00:10.402 --> 00:12.344
- I truly believe the island
was speaking to you.

00:12.421 --> 00:15.431
I would like to invite you
to stay on Fantasy Island.

00:17.852 --> 00:20.019
[birds chirping]

00:20.170 --> 00:23.413
<i> [gentle, bright music]</i>

00:23.432 --> 00:30.320
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:32.700 --> 00:35.183
- Uniforms?

00:35.944 --> 00:38.746
Nobody said nothing
about no damn uniform.

00:42.618 --> 00:44.501
[chuckles]

00:45.862 --> 00:48.088
Well, um...

00:50.292 --> 00:52.609
[laughs]

00:52.628 --> 00:58.282
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:58.284 --> 01:00.708
- Wow, look at you.
- [laughs]

01:00.786 --> 01:03.303
Eh?
Just a little something.

01:03.305 --> 01:04.471
- I know.

01:04.623 --> 01:06.381
- You know,
I haven't worn a uniform

01:06.458 --> 01:08.292
since I was in grade school,

01:08.294 --> 01:10.885
but I think
I can make this work.

01:10.963 --> 01:12.296
- Yes, you can.

01:12.298 --> 01:14.798
[both laugh]
Oh, there's the plane.

01:14.817 --> 01:16.992
Okay, let's go.

01:18.562 --> 01:21.563
[plane whirring]

01:21.582 --> 01:24.416
<i> [upbeat guitar music]</i>

01:24.568 --> 01:26.901
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:26.921 --> 01:28.812
- I know I'm new here,

01:28.831 --> 01:30.738
but isn't the dock
the other way?

01:30.758 --> 01:32.091
- Yeah, but sometimes,

01:32.167 --> 01:34.668
guests arrange
for an alternate arrival.

01:34.744 --> 01:36.762
- [chuckles]

01:42.103 --> 01:44.586
- Ruby, look up.

01:44.605 --> 01:46.012
- What?

01:46.089 --> 01:48.348
- I love my job.
I love it.

01:48.442 --> 01:51.685
That will be Daphne Madden and
Zev Randall of San Francisco.

01:51.761 --> 01:53.854
- Okay.

01:53.930 --> 01:55.839
You know,
Mel wanted to skydive once?

01:55.858 --> 01:56.782
- Huh?
- Uh-huh.

01:56.933 --> 01:58.342
Yeah, I told him he was crazy.

01:58.344 --> 02:00.268
- On Fantasy Island,
you'll find that it's best

02:00.346 --> 02:03.196
to meet people where they're at
without judgment.

02:03.273 --> 02:05.440
- Right.
Now, I sort of get what you do

02:05.517 --> 02:09.795
with all the making
the impossible possible stuff,

02:09.872 --> 02:12.965
but what exactly
am I supposed to do?

02:13.116 --> 02:16.451
- We have to figure
that out together.

02:16.470 --> 02:19.029
The island chose you to be here
to be my right hand.

02:19.031 --> 02:21.365
I'm guessing because you have
an intuitive way

02:21.383 --> 02:22.883
of knowing what's needed.

02:22.959 --> 02:24.810
- Well, I sure hope so.

02:24.887 --> 02:27.663
- Also, laugh at my jokes.

02:27.723 --> 02:29.648
- [laughs]
Done.

02:29.799 --> 02:31.817
- Just--just be you.

02:31.968 --> 02:34.044
Also, we have
one other guest today,

02:34.062 --> 02:35.896
so keep an eye
on the east bungalows

02:36.048 --> 02:37.990
this afternoon, please--
room 112.

02:38.141 --> 02:40.217
- Room 112.
Got it.

02:40.219 --> 02:42.327
- Oh, here they are.
Smiles.

02:42.479 --> 02:43.996
- Ah.

02:45.499 --> 02:47.557
- Whoo!
- Whoo!

02:47.559 --> 02:49.317
both: Whoo!

02:49.395 --> 02:51.461
- That was incredible.

02:53.582 --> 02:56.991
- Ms. Madden, Mr. Randall,
I'm Elena Roarke, your host.

02:57.069 --> 02:59.419
Welcome to Fantasy Island.

02:59.496 --> 03:02.422
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

03:02.499 --> 03:09.396
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:12.434 --> 03:15.585
So tell me.
What can the island do for you?

03:15.587 --> 03:18.179
- Well, our--our fantasy is
to have the ultimate adventure.

03:18.273 --> 03:21.107
- So not just any adventure,
but the ultimate.

03:21.260 --> 03:22.684
[laughter]
I like a challenge.

03:22.703 --> 03:24.352
- Well, I warn you.
We have a pretty high bar.

03:24.371 --> 03:27.522
- Yeah, we got married
at the top of Mount Kilimanjaro

03:27.599 --> 03:30.767
and we actually exchanged
carabiners instead of rings.

03:30.786 --> 03:31.952
It was incredibly romantic.

03:32.028 --> 03:33.212
- And we promised each other

03:33.363 --> 03:35.272
that the adventure
would never end.

03:35.290 --> 03:37.441
- And how is that
going for you?

03:37.443 --> 03:38.366
- We did it.

03:38.385 --> 03:39.943
We designed our life
to be free.

03:39.945 --> 03:42.203
No kids, no pets.
- Don't even own a fern.

03:42.281 --> 03:44.130
- Mm.
That's what you both wanted?

03:44.132 --> 03:46.450
- Yeah, 100%.
- Yep.

03:46.468 --> 03:50.804
- Wow, well, it sounds like
your life is a fantasy.

03:50.956 --> 03:52.397
- The thing is, um,

03:52.549 --> 03:54.791
we haven't been anywhere
in years.

03:54.810 --> 03:56.309
You know, jobs get in the way.

03:56.462 --> 03:58.812
Zev teaches literature
and I'm in sales.

03:58.888 --> 04:02.466
- Well, she'd be running her
division if she pushed for it.

04:02.468 --> 04:03.891
- Just waiting
for the right moment

04:03.911 --> 04:06.486
to make my move,
as we've discussed.

04:06.638 --> 04:08.080
- Um...

04:08.156 --> 04:11.141
Truth is, we--we haven't been
connecting in the ways

04:11.159 --> 04:14.478
we used to and--can I say?

04:14.480 --> 04:19.073
Um, we're not really
having sex anymore.

04:19.151 --> 04:21.651
- Yeah, we just wanna
be like we were

04:21.670 --> 04:24.154
at the top of Kilimanjaro.

04:24.156 --> 04:27.657
- We can make that happen,
yeah--

04:27.751 --> 04:29.159
she can, I assume.

04:29.177 --> 04:31.603
- I--I can.
Yeah, of course.

04:31.680 --> 04:34.756
But adventures of Fantasy Island
can be dangerous.

04:34.775 --> 04:37.017
You'll most likely see
each other in a new light.

04:37.169 --> 04:38.926
- Well, we're not afraid
of anything,

04:39.004 --> 04:41.113
so let the adventure begin.

04:41.264 --> 04:42.355
[laughter]

04:42.599 --> 04:44.616
- Your fantasy begins with
a rejuvenating treatment

04:44.768 --> 04:47.193
at our rainforest spa.
- Thank you so much.

04:47.270 --> 04:48.345
We really need this.
- Thank you.

04:48.347 --> 04:50.122
- You wouldn't be here
if you didn't.

04:50.273 --> 04:54.275
Nobody comes to Fantasy Island
by accident.

04:54.295 --> 04:55.127
- Well, okay.

04:55.354 --> 04:57.296
I am off to hover around
room 112.

04:57.447 --> 04:58.422
- Oh, thank you.

05:00.709 --> 05:02.042
- You know, I--
[laughs]

05:02.194 --> 05:04.952
It's just--it's just
the strangest feeling.

05:04.972 --> 05:08.640
A week ago,
I was like a dying old lady,

05:08.792 --> 05:10.809
and now I feel like a girl

05:10.886 --> 05:13.312
who just left home
for the first time.

05:13.463 --> 05:15.022
- Mm.

05:16.208 --> 05:17.465
- Good morning, Mrs. Akuda.

05:17.484 --> 05:21.061
- Oh, morning, Javier.
But I think it's just Ruby now.

05:21.137 --> 05:23.405
- Okay.
Yes, ma'am.

05:25.642 --> 05:28.309
- And how are you, Elena?

05:28.329 --> 05:31.054
- Is there a reason
I should be anything but fine?

05:31.056 --> 05:32.556
- [chuckles]
Come on.

05:32.574 --> 05:33.999
I know you're not
the biggest fan of change--

05:34.150 --> 05:36.150
or making new friends.

05:36.228 --> 05:39.412
- Oh, you mean Ruby?
I'm thrilled she's here.

05:39.565 --> 05:41.840
- Okay, good.
Just checking.

05:41.917 --> 05:44.009
- Yeah, we're gonna bond.
Girl time.

05:44.160 --> 05:46.011
- Girl time?
Bonding?

05:46.088 --> 05:47.012
- Yeah.

05:47.163 --> 05:49.514
- I thought that wasn't
your thing.

05:49.741 --> 05:51.424
Take it easy.

05:51.501 --> 05:52.684
- Mm-hmm.

05:52.761 --> 05:56.063
[dog panting]

05:56.857 --> 05:58.982
Girl time?

05:59.693 --> 06:02.069
[gong chimes]

06:04.865 --> 06:06.180
- Oh, this is nice.

06:06.200 --> 06:08.274
- I know.
I'm so relaxed.

06:08.351 --> 06:11.428
Beats you grading papers
till midnight.

06:11.430 --> 06:16.116
- And you seething about
Tim promoting Steve over you.

06:16.192 --> 06:18.543
- Wow.
Less relaxed.

06:21.215 --> 06:23.382
I mean, is something
supposed to happen?

06:23.609 --> 06:25.291
- I don't know, maybe
the adventure starts tomorrow.

06:25.368 --> 06:28.612
Look, I'm sorry
about the Steve thing.

06:28.614 --> 06:30.947
- It's fine.

06:30.949 --> 06:32.891
- I love you.

06:32.968 --> 06:35.877
<i> [mystical music]</i>

06:35.896 --> 06:37.879
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:37.898 --> 06:40.732
- [gasps]
What just happened?

06:40.884 --> 06:41.975
- Oh, my God.

06:42.127 --> 06:43.902
I'm you!
- I'm you!

06:43.979 --> 06:46.554
[yelping]
I'm you!

06:46.573 --> 06:48.407
- Tha--tha--that's mine!

06:48.483 --> 06:49.649
She "Face/Off"-ed us!

06:49.801 --> 06:51.818
- This isn't "Face/Off."
This is "Freaky Friday."

06:51.970 --> 06:54.061
She "Freaky Friday"-ed us!

06:54.139 --> 06:56.415
- How did they do it?
- Ugh, I'm so hairy.

06:56.491 --> 06:57.416
<i> [quirky music]</i>

06:57.567 --> 06:58.900
- Oh.

06:58.919 --> 07:01.420
Wow, these look different
from up here.

07:01.571 --> 07:02.587
Heavy.

07:02.664 --> 07:03.588
- Let's see
if we can change back.

07:03.815 --> 07:05.907
Kiss me.

07:05.926 --> 07:07.259
- That would be a no.
- Oh, my God.

07:07.410 --> 07:08.985
I just realized
I can pee standing up.

07:09.004 --> 07:12.413
- Okay, all right,
there's more to men than...

07:12.433 --> 07:13.915
what?

07:13.992 --> 07:16.417
What are you--what are you
looking at me like that for?

07:16.495 --> 07:18.678
- I'm looking at me.
I don't look half bad.

07:18.830 --> 07:19.846
Turn around.

07:19.998 --> 07:21.331
- I thought my guns
were more impressive.

07:21.333 --> 07:24.276
That's a little bit
of a disappointment.

07:24.427 --> 07:27.170
- I mean, I knew this was gonna
be a physical challenge,

07:27.172 --> 07:30.356
but I had no idea
it would be like this.

07:30.433 --> 07:34.119
Well, Roarke said this could
be a dangerous adventure.

07:34.196 --> 07:37.330
Looking through your eyes,
what am I gonna discover?

07:44.873 --> 07:46.173
- Hmm.

07:47.784 --> 07:49.042
Oh, hello.

07:49.194 --> 07:50.877
Believe I've been told
to keep an eye out for you.

07:50.954 --> 07:52.212
- [sighs]
You're new.

07:52.364 --> 07:55.248
- That's right.
Can I help you?

07:55.309 --> 07:56.975
- You can tell Roarke
I'm awake.

07:57.126 --> 07:59.269
Thank you.
[clears throat]

08:00.797 --> 08:02.230
- Oh, I...

08:03.725 --> 08:06.634
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

08:06.712 --> 08:13.492
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:17.998 --> 08:20.332
[shaver whirring]

08:30.902 --> 08:32.585
- This is harder
than I thought.

08:32.662 --> 08:35.572
Oh, this is messy.

08:35.590 --> 08:37.090
[toilet flushes]

08:37.166 --> 08:39.075
- I feel like you can
pull off bangs.

08:39.094 --> 08:40.835
- You mess with my hair,
you die.

08:40.912 --> 08:42.854
<i> [quirky music]</i>

08:43.006 --> 08:47.917
So I'm you and you're me.

08:47.936 --> 08:49.361
What should we do next?
- I don't know.

08:49.512 --> 08:53.439
We got all that banana stuff
on us, so...

08:53.516 --> 08:58.928
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:58.930 --> 09:01.614
Wanna join me in the shower?

09:01.767 --> 09:04.951
- Is this how you feel
every time you see me naked?

09:05.103 --> 09:06.619
'Cause this is intense.

09:06.696 --> 09:09.606
- I told you.
Men are visual creatures.

09:09.699 --> 09:10.790
- You really are.

09:10.942 --> 09:13.701
- Okay, this is disorienting,

09:13.720 --> 09:16.780
but, like, weirdly arousing.

09:16.798 --> 09:18.298
- Should we give it a try?

09:18.450 --> 09:20.541
- It's the adventurous thing
to do.

09:20.561 --> 09:22.394
[both moaning]

09:22.545 --> 09:25.730
Wow, you're like
a teenager again.

09:25.807 --> 09:28.567
- You too, but extra.

09:28.643 --> 09:30.794
- [grunts]
Oh, yeah.

09:30.812 --> 09:33.479
Oh, you weigh a lot.

09:33.632 --> 09:35.240
I weigh a lot, I guess.

09:35.317 --> 09:37.483
[grunts]
This is--

09:37.578 --> 09:38.484
[sighs]
Much better.

09:38.637 --> 09:40.036
All right, kiss me.

09:41.915 --> 09:43.564
I can kiss for hours.

09:43.584 --> 09:45.141
- Really?
'Cause I'm feeling, like,

09:45.143 --> 09:46.901
a certain momentum happening.

09:46.920 --> 09:48.494
- Yeah, well--okay, all right.

09:48.647 --> 09:49.979
Yeah, no, that's not good.

09:49.998 --> 09:52.591
Wait, "that's not good"?
I do that to you all the time.

09:52.667 --> 09:54.834
- Oh, right. Yeah, sorry.
No, that's not good.

09:54.911 --> 09:56.243
- Why didn't you say anything?

09:56.263 --> 09:57.745
- Baby, I don't like
to make waves.

09:57.764 --> 09:59.656
- Right. Yeah.

09:59.658 --> 10:01.749
- But I do always tell you
to go slower.

10:01.827 --> 10:04.344
- Okay.
I get that now.

10:04.496 --> 10:05.662
What?

10:05.664 --> 10:07.272
Oh, you're done.

10:07.423 --> 10:09.499
- [panting]
I'm done.

10:09.501 --> 10:11.684
- All right, just,

10:11.837 --> 10:13.612
gotta learn control, babe.

10:13.763 --> 10:15.780
- I'm sorry.

10:15.857 --> 10:19.600
<i> [gentle music]</i>

10:19.678 --> 10:21.511
- It's fine.

10:21.529 --> 10:23.363
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:23.515 --> 10:25.457
[crying softly]

10:25.608 --> 10:27.250
Why am I crying?

10:30.964 --> 10:33.022
[knocking at door]

10:33.041 --> 10:36.468
- Good afternoon,
Mr. Randall, Ms. Madden.

10:36.619 --> 10:37.802
Has your fantasy begun?

10:37.879 --> 10:38.970
- Oh, you know it has.

10:39.122 --> 10:40.713
- You called us
by the right names.

10:40.790 --> 10:42.548
- And is it exhilarating?

10:42.550 --> 10:44.534
You know, like being
in Kilimanjaro?

10:44.552 --> 10:45.477
- Well, it's, uh--

10:45.628 --> 10:47.036
- No, no, no, it's--
it's too much.

10:47.130 --> 10:48.129
I mean,
I can feel this testosterone

10:48.206 --> 10:49.372
just going through my veins

10:49.391 --> 10:51.316
and it's just making me
feel pissed!

10:51.393 --> 10:54.711
- Oh, okay, well, you learn
to regulate those effects.

10:54.729 --> 10:56.303
It's okay.
- Well, I hope so,

10:56.305 --> 10:58.823
because he keeps--
I mean, it's unbelievable.

10:58.975 --> 11:00.158
- I keep bursting into tears.

11:00.235 --> 11:01.993
- What is that?
I don't do that.

11:02.070 --> 11:03.236
- I don't know.
I'm sorry.

11:03.388 --> 11:05.146
- You're giving women
a bad name.

11:05.165 --> 11:07.499
- Okay, I got it.
[stammers] I'm good.

11:07.575 --> 11:10.894
- And, Ms. Madden, how are you
adjusting to this new reality?

11:10.912 --> 11:12.412
- [scoffs]
Well, for one thing,

11:12.564 --> 11:14.564
there's a sort of dull pain
that won't go away.

11:14.566 --> 11:17.008
We are taking you to
a cardiologist when we're back.

11:17.160 --> 11:19.252
I'm telling you right now.

11:19.328 --> 11:20.261
[sighs]

11:22.516 --> 11:25.425
- Daphne and I are blown away
by this adventure,

11:25.501 --> 11:28.261
we really are,
but ready to switch back now.

11:28.413 --> 11:29.336
- Well, the thing is,

11:29.431 --> 11:31.748
every fantasy
runs a natural course,

11:31.766 --> 11:35.009
and yours has just begun.

11:35.028 --> 11:37.344
So try to enjoy it.
It's a great adventure.

11:37.364 --> 11:38.755
I mean, you really
haven't walked a mile

11:38.773 --> 11:40.365
in each other's shoes yet.

11:40.516 --> 11:43.276
- Set your whole foot down.
Don't lead with your heel.

11:43.428 --> 11:44.869
Why is your back bent over
like that?

11:45.021 --> 11:47.038
- Oh, that would be
from the agonizing pain.

11:47.115 --> 11:49.265
These make no sense.
- I can't with these shorts.

11:49.267 --> 11:52.101
Do you tuck the leg in
to the other leg or just--

11:52.120 --> 11:54.771
- No, no, no, don't--
don't bunch 'em up.

11:54.773 --> 11:56.439
What are you doing to my ass?

11:56.458 --> 11:57.549
Come on--oh!

11:57.700 --> 11:59.884
[both shouting]
Oh, God!

11:59.961 --> 12:01.720
- Here, just sit down.

12:01.722 --> 12:03.112
Just sit down.

12:03.131 --> 12:05.223
Do your makeup
while I get impatient

12:05.374 --> 12:07.283
because my face
can just walk out the door

12:07.285 --> 12:10.061
without needing to do
a damn thing to it.

12:10.138 --> 12:12.305
- You think I can't do this?

12:12.457 --> 12:15.900
I'm the master of lip balm.
Watch this.

12:16.127 --> 12:17.384
Huh?
- That's actually pretty good.

12:17.404 --> 12:18.461
- Yeah, yeah.

12:18.480 --> 12:20.405
- That's hot.
Why is that hot?

12:22.484 --> 12:23.908
- Please.

12:24.060 --> 12:25.910
- Here you are, sir.

12:27.080 --> 12:29.080
- You see that?
He didn't even look at me.

12:29.157 --> 12:30.656
It's like I wasn't even here.

12:30.733 --> 12:32.658
- Yeah, welcome to my life.
Wait, no, no, no.

12:32.735 --> 12:35.420
I want the whole
He-Man experience.

12:37.832 --> 12:39.591
- [chuckles]

12:41.669 --> 12:43.486
- Did you see me flexing?

12:43.488 --> 12:46.914
- [chuckles]
Correction, I saw me flexing.

12:46.933 --> 12:49.008
Also, I--I get what
you liked about

12:49.085 --> 12:50.843
watching me put make up on.

12:50.920 --> 12:52.845
I think Roarke is right.

12:52.998 --> 12:54.439
This is gonna bring us closer.

12:54.516 --> 12:56.941
- Well, it's hard not to be
honest with each other

12:57.018 --> 12:59.027
when we are each other.

13:01.430 --> 13:03.072
- That guy is staring at me.

13:05.360 --> 13:07.952
Do you think he can tell?

13:08.029 --> 13:09.287
- No,
I don't think he can tell.

13:09.364 --> 13:11.122
I think he's just
checking you out.

13:11.199 --> 13:12.439
- Really?

13:12.534 --> 13:14.942
- That guy better keep his eye
on his own dinner.

13:14.961 --> 13:18.521
- Well, well, well,
you're jealous.

13:18.540 --> 13:19.798
- Let's just order.

13:19.874 --> 13:22.875
- [laughs]

13:23.028 --> 13:25.711
<i> [gentle music]</i>

13:25.788 --> 13:33.019
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:36.983 --> 13:39.967
- Hope it's all right
to give him people food.

13:39.986 --> 13:42.362
- It's perfectly fine.
[chuckles]

13:44.732 --> 13:46.883
- [sighs]

13:46.901 --> 13:49.143
You look the same.

