the right questions to ask.

28:26.096 --> 28:28.872
That's gonna be
a useful skill in this job.

28:29.024 --> 28:30.432
- I'm sorry.
I'm prying.

28:30.451 --> 28:32.692
- It's okay.

28:32.712 --> 28:34.619
I was engaged once,

28:34.772 --> 28:37.622
but I had to choose between

28:37.699 --> 28:40.968
the island and him.

28:41.962 --> 28:45.222
- You chose the island?

28:47.618 --> 28:49.709
- Something like that.
[timer dings]

28:49.787 --> 28:52.563
Oh.
Let's eat.

28:52.672 --> 28:55.715
<i> [upbeat music playing]</i>

28:55.793 --> 28:57.476
- Excuse me.

28:57.628 --> 28:59.962
I'm looking for my wife,
Daphne.

28:59.980 --> 29:02.889
She might've been here earlier.

29:02.967 --> 29:04.224
- Wife?
- Husband.

29:04.301 --> 29:06.635
I mean--I mean, husband.
I call him Daphne.

29:06.728 --> 29:08.061
- Yeah, that guy.

29:08.138 --> 29:09.747
He got into a fight
with some regulars,

29:09.898 --> 29:11.064
so I tossed them all out.

29:11.083 --> 29:12.583
- What?
When was this?

29:12.734 --> 29:13.900
- A couple hours ago?

29:13.978 --> 29:15.753
I mean,
if he's still not back,

29:15.904 --> 29:16.979
the jerks might've done
a jungle toss.

29:16.997 --> 29:18.088
They think it's funny.

29:18.165 --> 29:19.664
- What's a jungle toss?
What is that?

29:19.817 --> 29:21.925
- You drive a drunk person
out into the jungle

29:22.077 --> 29:23.927
and you toss them
on the far side.

29:24.004 --> 29:25.763
They usually travel back
in a day or two.

29:25.914 --> 29:28.414
- Okay, yeah--what?
Oh, God!

29:28.434 --> 29:30.842
- So you're human?

29:30.919 --> 29:32.661
I mean, totally human?

29:32.663 --> 29:34.329
- You know,
I'd prick a finger for you,

29:34.331 --> 29:37.107
but the napkins are new.

29:37.259 --> 29:42.279
- The island, it's magic,
and you're like a conduit?

29:42.356 --> 29:45.173
[chuckles]
Okay, but are there rules?

29:45.192 --> 29:48.935
You know, like,
do things always turn out?

29:48.954 --> 29:52.105
- Depends on your definition
of turn out.

29:52.182 --> 29:54.958
- Well, is it possible that

29:55.035 --> 29:57.185
Zev and Daphne
would be happier apart

29:57.187 --> 30:02.257
and the island is just
showing them that bigger truth?

30:03.710 --> 30:05.285
- It's possible, yes.

30:05.304 --> 30:08.380
- Yeah, but would the island
really do that?

30:08.532 --> 30:11.457
You know, separate a couple
that loves each other?

30:11.535 --> 30:12.976
Is that right?

30:13.128 --> 30:15.103
- It did you and Mel.

30:16.631 --> 30:19.391
<i> [gentle music]</i>

30:19.467 --> 30:21.043
- Yes, well, you know, that--

30:21.061 --> 30:24.321
that was a little more
complicated.

30:24.472 --> 30:25.564
- There you go.

30:25.716 --> 30:27.549
It happens,

30:27.551 --> 30:30.577
and it can be complicated.

30:33.724 --> 30:35.607
- Did it to you?

30:35.759 --> 30:38.818
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:38.896 --> 30:41.338
- Anyway.

30:41.415 --> 30:45.417
You know, this island is--
it's more than a job.

30:45.493 --> 30:46.844
It's a calling.

30:46.995 --> 30:49.404
You know what?
Think of it as Joan of Arc,

30:49.423 --> 30:51.756
but with less
burning at the stake--

30:51.833 --> 30:54.259
at least, so far.

30:54.336 --> 30:56.854
- You know, didn't you say
that the person

30:56.930 --> 31:00.749
Mr. Lee lost was his fiancée?

31:00.767 --> 31:03.935
It's just a very specific
experience to share,

31:04.012 --> 31:05.362
so, you know,
maybe that's why

31:05.589 --> 31:09.992
you found his fantasy
such a difficult one.

31:16.600 --> 31:18.783
- Daphne!

31:18.860 --> 31:20.693
Oh, Daph!

31:20.713 --> 31:23.438
- [whimpers]

31:23.457 --> 31:25.273
- Daphne!

31:25.275 --> 31:27.626
Oh, thank God.
Oh, thank God you're alive.

31:27.778 --> 31:28.960
Oh!

31:29.037 --> 31:30.795
- Zev, the guy
from the restaurant,

31:30.872 --> 31:32.038
he punched me in the face

31:32.116 --> 31:33.223
and I don't even know
how I got up here

31:33.375 --> 31:34.874
and I think I'm so drunk
and I'm sorry.

31:34.894 --> 31:36.134
- Okay.
Okay, okay, okay.

31:36.286 --> 31:38.711
It's okay.
Just climb down here.

31:38.731 --> 31:40.288
I gotta tell you something.

31:40.290 --> 31:42.140
- No.
There's animals down there.

31:42.217 --> 31:45.068
There's growly,
slithery animals down there.

31:45.145 --> 31:46.628
- All right, I'm coming up.

31:46.630 --> 31:50.056
[animals chattering]

31:50.075 --> 31:53.410
Oh, thank God, Daphne.
Thank God you're all right.

31:53.637 --> 31:55.412
Come here.
Come here.

32:02.146 --> 32:04.813
- Thought you were afraid.

32:04.831 --> 32:07.591
- Uh, of jungle predators?
Hell yeah.

32:07.668 --> 32:11.153
- No, not jungle predators.

32:11.155 --> 32:14.932
I figured it out tonight
what this weird pain is.

32:15.008 --> 32:17.008
You were scared
a lot of the time,

32:17.161 --> 32:19.478
but mostly around me.

32:21.832 --> 32:23.982
- Uh...

32:26.503 --> 32:28.946
Yeah.

32:29.097 --> 32:32.507
I'm afraid I'll lose you
all the time.

32:32.526 --> 32:34.600
<i> [tender music]</i>

32:34.678 --> 32:36.936
- Honey, I'm right here,

32:36.956 --> 32:40.031
and I'm not going anywhere.

32:40.184 --> 32:43.627
I need you to be less scared

32:43.704 --> 32:46.538
to open up to me, all right?

32:46.690 --> 32:47.856
Figure out
what you're feeling

32:47.858 --> 32:49.967
and just tell me.

32:50.118 --> 32:52.711
I'll be okay.
It'll be all right.

32:52.787 --> 32:55.621
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:55.641 --> 32:58.416
- Uh, okay.

32:58.494 --> 33:00.435
Right now...

33:02.889 --> 33:04.815
I'm feeling pregnant.

33:04.891 --> 33:07.709
- What?
- Yeah.

33:07.728 --> 33:10.378
There's a baby in here.

33:10.397 --> 33:11.713
- But we don't want a baby.

33:11.715 --> 33:13.306
- Well, it's why
you've been so tired.

33:13.400 --> 33:14.733
It's why I've been crying
all the time.

33:14.809 --> 33:16.660
- It's not what we planned.
- Well, it--it can be.

33:16.811 --> 33:19.145
You know, we could turn
the study into a nursery.

33:19.223 --> 33:20.905
- No, no, no, this is--
you're not listening to me.

33:21.058 --> 33:23.125
Listen, I don't want a baby!

33:29.657 --> 33:30.565
- You don't want a baby?

33:30.584 --> 33:32.584
- You know when I wanted
a baby?

33:32.660 --> 33:34.236
When we first met.

33:34.254 --> 33:36.071
- You said you didn't want
a baby, so...

33:36.089 --> 33:37.756
- No,<i> you</i> didn't want a baby.

33:37.908 --> 33:39.074
- Okay, well, you know what?

33:39.076 --> 33:40.925
I--I don't--
I don't know what to say.

33:41.078 --> 33:44.003
Being in this body, you know,

33:44.081 --> 33:46.172
feeling this
little person growing,

33:46.250 --> 33:48.917
I just--I--I can't explain it.

33:48.919 --> 33:53.104
I changed my mind.

33:53.181 --> 33:55.940
- This is the speech
I'm gonna give to Tim

33:56.017 --> 33:58.927
telling him
I don't just want California.

33:58.945 --> 34:02.614
I want the whole
western sales region.

34:02.766 --> 34:04.783
And I want this.

34:04.859 --> 34:07.711
And this and that,

34:07.862 --> 34:10.530
they don't go together.

34:10.549 --> 34:12.215
- But they could.

34:12.292 --> 34:14.217
Daph, it'll be 50/50.

34:14.369 --> 34:15.701
- No, no, it's--
- Yeah, we can do it.

34:15.779 --> 34:18.221
- It's never--it's never 50/50.

34:18.373 --> 34:21.283
When a man and a woman
each have demanding careers,

34:21.301 --> 34:24.119
it's always the woman
who's got to give up

34:24.121 --> 34:26.805
just a little bit more.

34:26.881 --> 34:28.623
And once the woman
gives that up,

34:28.716 --> 34:31.026
she never gets it back.

34:33.238 --> 34:36.314
I might've been fine with it
before this trip,

34:36.466 --> 34:39.409
but now that I know
what it feels like

34:39.486 --> 34:43.896
to be powerful and confident,

34:43.916 --> 34:46.583
all the stuff
that you take for granted,

34:46.660 --> 34:49.735
I want to go for this.

34:49.755 --> 34:53.590
- I--I really want this baby.

34:53.741 --> 34:57.410
- So what do we do?

34:57.429 --> 34:58.762
- I don't know.

35:01.583 --> 35:03.749
But this new you?

35:03.844 --> 35:07.312
Seriously turning me on.

35:07.463 --> 35:10.181
- I love you.

35:10.334 --> 35:13.351
<i> [mystical music]</i>

35:13.503 --> 35:20.367
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:22.028 --> 35:24.696
- Oh, thank God.
Oh, thank God.

35:24.772 --> 35:25.771
- Oh, my God, I'm me.

35:25.791 --> 35:27.182
I'm me again.
- Ow, my eye.

35:27.184 --> 35:29.200
- Oh, how I'm me again.
Thank God.

35:29.353 --> 35:31.986
Oh, honey, come here.
Let me kiss it better.

35:32.038 --> 35:34.339
Oh, my gosh, look at you.

35:39.138 --> 35:41.138
- Now that I've been
inside your body,

35:41.289 --> 35:42.864
prepare to have
your mind blown.

35:42.883 --> 35:44.182
- Okay, shh.

35:44.259 --> 35:45.791
Show, don't tell.

35:45.811 --> 35:48.186
- [chuckles]

35:50.056 --> 35:51.706
- I'm not letting you
go back to sleep

35:51.725 --> 35:53.733
if you don't talk to me.

36:02.736 --> 36:06.479
It was your fault, wasn't it?

36:06.498 --> 36:08.665
That's what
you can't live with.

36:18.068 --> 36:22.070
- The road was open.
It was dark.

36:22.072 --> 36:24.255
She was half asleep next to me.

36:24.408 --> 36:26.666
I leaned over
to give her a kiss.

36:26.685 --> 36:28.167
And I crossed the lane,

36:28.261 --> 36:32.230
and suddenly there was a truck
where there wasn't one before.

36:36.528 --> 36:40.071
So yeah, totally my fault.

36:41.867 --> 36:43.775
Thanks for bringing that up.

36:43.927 --> 36:47.111
- I know what it is to...

36:47.188 --> 36:51.291
hurt someone
and feel the guilt.

36:53.119 --> 36:55.861
Once upon a time, I--

36:55.881 --> 36:58.773
I hurt my own fiancé.

36:58.775 --> 37:01.459
- You didn't kill him.

37:01.611 --> 37:04.779
- But I broke his heart.

37:04.798 --> 37:07.115
I don't know, I see my pain
as a kind of penance,

37:07.117 --> 37:11.228
as what I owe for what I did.

37:11.455 --> 37:12.896
- And next is the part
where you tell me

37:12.973 --> 37:14.472
that Olivia wouldn't want this,

37:14.624 --> 37:17.883
that she'd kick my ass
to see me wasting my life.

37:17.961 --> 37:19.569
Yeah, it's true.

37:19.646 --> 37:23.631
But what she wants
doesn't matter anymore

37:23.633 --> 37:25.242
because she's dead.

37:25.393 --> 37:30.896
- Mr. Lee, I wouldn't have
given you this fantasy.

37:30.974 --> 37:32.490
At the end,

37:32.567 --> 37:36.086
the only real way
out of the pain is...

37:36.162 --> 37:39.163
you have to go through it.

37:39.240 --> 37:42.575
- There's no way
through this pain.

37:42.594 --> 37:45.153
It's not a swamp.

37:45.155 --> 37:48.914
It's a wall.
[sighs]

37:48.934 --> 37:51.917
<i> [melancholic music]</i>

37:51.995 --> 37:59.150
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:00.020 --> 38:02.028
- Tell me about her.

38:05.617 --> 38:08.359
- She wanted to be in fashion.

38:08.436 --> 38:12.747
She made all her own clothes.

38:14.793 --> 38:17.035
She was making
her own wedding dress.

38:17.187 --> 38:20.446
I kept telling her it's bad luck
for me to see her in it.

38:20.524 --> 38:22.857
[both chuckle]

38:22.876 --> 38:25.951
She kept making it
and remaking it

38:25.971 --> 38:28.638
and asking my opinion.

38:28.790 --> 38:31.641
The last one had sequins.

38:31.793 --> 38:35.127
[chuckles]
She hated it.

38:35.147 --> 38:39.399
She was gonna tear it apart,
start over.

38:41.969 --> 38:44.303
But it was the last one,

38:44.381 --> 38:46.698
so they buried her in it.

38:52.556 --> 38:53.888
[sighs]

38:53.890 --> 38:57.742
She's in the ground in sequins.

38:57.836 --> 39:05.133
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:27.515 --> 39:30.441
<i> [mellow music]</i>

39:30.518 --> 39:36.188
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:36.208 --> 39:40.210
- Well, it's nice to see you
both back in your own bodies.

39:40.286 --> 39:42.879
- And I hear congratulations
are in order.

39:43.030 --> 39:46.049
- They are.
We're having a baby.

39:46.126 --> 39:48.218
It still sounds
so strange to say.

39:48.294 --> 39:50.278
- We decided
I'm gonna be the anchor parent,

39:50.296 --> 39:52.204
basically like
a stay-at-home dad.

39:52.224 --> 39:55.783
- Well, I made homemade baby
food for all of my grandkids,

39:55.802 --> 39:58.286
so I'll send you some recipes.

39:58.304 --> 39:59.454
- Hmm?

39:59.456 --> 40:01.881
- Oh, I'm older than I look.

40:01.900 --> 40:04.308
- I'm so glad
everything worked out.

40:04.461 --> 40:05.885
It usually does.

40:05.962 --> 40:07.737
- We're ready to load up.

40:07.889 --> 40:09.814
Elena.
- Javier.

40:09.891 --> 40:16.413
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:16.564 --> 40:17.989
- Take it from a woman.

40:18.065 --> 40:20.491
She definitely sees you.

40:20.568 --> 40:23.962
- I was briefly a woman,
and I agree.

40:28.760 --> 40:31.819
<i> [gentle music]</i>

40:31.821 --> 40:35.323
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:35.325 --> 40:39.102
- Oh, he could still be coming.
[chuckles]

40:39.137 --> 40:40.662
- I really tried.

40:40.664 --> 40:45.424
- Got five more years to make
a game plan for next time.

40:45.444 --> 40:47.777
- Wait.

40:47.929 --> 40:50.672
- Mr. Lee.

40:50.690 --> 40:52.340
You're leaving us?

40:52.342 --> 40:55.009
- Talking helped a little--
enough.

40:55.028 --> 40:58.455
- Mr. Lee, you won't get back
what you lost,

40:58.531 --> 41:00.957
but you can create
something new.

41:01.108 --> 41:04.944
- Yeah.
Maybe.

41:04.963 --> 41:07.380
Thank you.
- Of course.

41:10.785 --> 41:11.859
[sighs]

41:11.920 --> 41:16.881
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:17.033 --> 41:18.808
- I think we make a good team.

41:18.960 --> 41:21.369
- Not bad.

41:21.462 --> 41:28.318
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:29.988 --> 41:33.031
My fiancé was named James.

41:35.660 --> 41:38.720
- That's a good name.

41:38.722 --> 41:43.057
- He had this great laugh
and beautiful blue eyes,

41:43.059 --> 41:45.168
and he still does.

41:45.245 --> 41:47.745
I mean, I--I assume.

41:47.897 --> 41:49.747
- [chuckles]

41:49.899 --> 41:53.568
And what else?

41:53.570 --> 41:56.904
- He liked carnival games and,
you know, a couple of times,

41:56.906 --> 42:00.091
he--he won
this big, stuffed animal,

42:00.185 --> 42:02.093
and he didn't know
what to do with it,

42:02.245 --> 42:05.337
so he asked me
if I could keep it.

42:05.415 --> 42:08.916
Said I needed a little--
a little whimsy in my life.

42:08.918 --> 42:10.601
But I mean,
what am I supposed to do

42:10.754 --> 42:13.104
with a giant pink elephant?

42:13.180 --> 42:15.448
Nothing, right? So I said no.
- [laughs]
